TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {11413=Automated data collection procedures for the survey were introduced in NHANES 2003–2004. In the MECs and analytical laboratories, data for the laboratory component are recorded directly onto a computerized data collection form. The system is centrally integrated, and it allows for ongoing monitoring of much of the data. Although the complete blood count and pregnancy analyses are performed in the MEC laboratory, most analyses are conducted elsewhere by approximately 21 laboratories across the United States., 8897=The NHANES QA/QC protocols meet the 1988 Clinical Laboratory Improvement Act mandates.
